Hi @everyone,

We want to let you know of a **change to Empawrium** which we will be rolling out 00:00 UTC. 

When @Ghost089  built Empawrium, he had a system for ensuring that the minting of the NFT’s was covered by the NFT creator. This was done by employing the Empawrium Token; an NFT creator would purchase Empawrium Tokens (1 ET = 2 MEWC) and use these to mint their NFTs. The costs are as follows:

 - **Unique NFT**: 5 Empawrium Tokens
 - **Multi-NFT**: 100 Empawrium Tokens

To reward the Meowcoin community for their patience and to help everyone have a chance to make a collection first up, **we disabled this feature for the week**. However, the time has come to reenable it to cover our operating costs (NFT minting, servers, etc). 

Starting from tomorrow, if you wish to create an NFT, you need to buy Empawrium Tokens to do so. Additionally, **we'll be dropping the site fee to 3% **(from the current 6%) to ensure Empawrium is one of the cheapest and most affordable NFT marketplaces in crypto.

We realise this might be a little confusing to some, so please feel free to ask in #empawrium-support any Q’s. I also apologise this wasn’t communicated well initially; this was a stuff up on my part so forgive me for this. 

Otherwise, Empawrium's launch has been a great success and we really appreciate all the love and effort that you guys have put into the work. Its taking all my self-control not to buy the entire damn store haha.

Cheers
